1
00:00:01,040 --> 00:00:02,760
I do as they tell me
and the street is safe.

2
00:00:02,840 --> 00:00:04,200
Who are they?

3
00:00:04,280 --> 00:00:05,520
I never meant for anyone to get hurt.

4
00:00:06,080 --> 00:00:07,560
(RAVEN CROWING)

5
00:00:07,640 --> 00:00:08,720
(WHISPERS) Let me be brave.

6
00:00:10,560 --> 00:00:12,920
Is it a trap? Is it a torture chamber?

7
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:16,400
If you were any part of killing her
and you're not afraid,

8
00:00:16,480 --> 00:00:17,760
then you understand nothing at all.

9
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:19,000
(ICE CRACKS)

10
00:00:23,200 --> 00:00:26,480
DOCTOR: Go to the city.
Tell them I'm back.

11
00:00:26,560 --> 00:00:28,480
Tell them I know what they did.

12
00:01:05,960 --> 00:01:08,800
(MUSIC PLAYING OVER RADIO)

13
00:01:13,720 --> 00:01:14,720
(DOOR CLOSES)

14
00:01:15,120 --> 00:01:17,760
# Don't stop me now

15
00:01:17,840 --> 00:01:20,360
# I'm having such a good time

16
00:01:20,440 --> 00:01:21,880
# I'm having a ball #

17
00:01:21,960 --> 00:01:23,000
Hi.

18
00:01:25,200 --> 00:01:26,200
What can I get you?

19
00:01:26,760 --> 00:01:29,320
I don't have any money.

20
00:01:29,560 --> 00:01:30,840
But I play.

21
00:01:32,720 --> 00:01:33,720
Okay.

22
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:40,240
Don't you need to plug that thing in?

23
00:01:41,800 --> 00:01:43,280
Yeah.

24
00:01:44,640 --> 00:01:46,120
(GLASSES WHIRRING)

25
00:01:47,560 --> 00:01:48,600
You're English.

26
00:01:49,880 --> 00:01:50,880
You're not?

27
00:01:52,840 --> 00:01:53,960
How did you get out here?

28
00:01:54,040 --> 00:01:55,240
Magic.

29
00:01:56,720 --> 00:01:59,400
Or maybe I went to an airport
and caught a plane.

30
00:01:59,960 --> 00:02:01,800
-Ah. (CHUCKLES)
-You?

31
00:02:03,920 --> 00:02:04,960
Magic.

32
00:02:06,400 --> 00:02:08,120
(RADIO CRACKLES)

33
00:02:12,600 --> 00:02:13,600
I believe you.

34
00:02:18,200 --> 00:02:19,680
-You been travelling?
-Yeah.

35
00:02:20,200 --> 00:02:21,680
From time to time.

36
00:02:30,320 --> 00:02:31,360
Is it a sad song?

37
00:02:32,520 --> 00:02:34,000
Nothing's sad till it's over.

38
00:02:34,920 --> 00:02:36,400
Then everything is.

39
00:02:42,040 --> 00:02:43,080
What's it called?

40
00:02:45,960 --> 00:02:47,880
I think that it's called...

41
00:02:47,960 --> 00:02:49,080
Clara.

42
00:02:50,800 --> 00:02:51,800
Tell me about her.

43
00:02:54,280 --> 00:02:56,280
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

44
00:03:57,600 --> 00:03:59,600
(WIND WHISTLING)

45
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:07,880
(BELLS TOLLING)

46
00:04:15,760 --> 00:04:17,280
Lord President.

47
00:04:18,040 --> 00:04:21,800
Are all the bells ringing?
The whole Cloister?

48
00:04:21,880 --> 00:04:23,200
What's going on down there?

49
00:04:23,560 --> 00:04:25,720
(BELLS TOLLING)

50
00:04:26,560 --> 00:04:28,400
GASTRON: I'm on my way
down to the Matrix now, sir.

51
00:04:28,480 --> 00:04:29,840
GENERAL: Keep the perimeter.

52
00:04:29,920 --> 00:04:31,600
It's okay to be afraid
down there, soldier.

53
00:04:31,680 --> 00:04:33,200
Sliders are everywhere, sir.

54
00:04:33,280 --> 00:04:34,520
Loads of those things.

55
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:36,640
GENERAL: Language, please.
I'm with the President.

56
00:04:36,720 --> 00:04:39,240
Sorry, sir.
The Cloister Wraiths are active.

57
00:04:39,320 --> 00:04:42,160
Do not approach them. Don't even
enter the Cloister. Just tell me.

58
00:04:42,480 --> 00:04:43,760
Are all the bells ringing?

59
00:04:43,840 --> 00:04:45,120
Yes, sir.

60
00:04:45,200 --> 00:04:47,920
Then we are facing great danger.

61
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:50,000
The Cloister Wraiths seem to think so.

62
00:04:50,080 --> 00:04:52,360
So where is he?

63
00:04:52,440 --> 00:04:53,640
Where has the Doctor gone?

64
00:04:53,960 --> 00:04:55,760
Back to the beginning, I should think.

65
00:04:56,960 --> 00:05:00,040
The Sisterhood of Karn has
no business in this chamber

66
00:05:00,120 --> 00:05:01,320
or on this planet.

67
00:05:01,400 --> 00:05:03,560
I heard the Doctor had come home.

68
00:05:03,640 --> 00:05:05,240
One so loves fireworks.

69
00:05:05,560 --> 00:05:06,760
(SCOFFS)

70
00:05:09,800 --> 00:05:12,000
(BELLS TOLLING IN DISTANCE)

71
00:05:41,720 --> 00:05:43,800
Why are they ringing all the bells?

72
00:05:43,880 --> 00:05:45,640
Never heard so many.

73
00:05:45,720 --> 00:05:49,680
What's gone wrong this time?
All the fuss they're always making.

74
00:05:50,680 --> 00:05:53,000
You up there.
You're not supposed to be there.

75
00:05:53,080 --> 00:05:55,760
I've only just put all that back,
it's for the boys.

76
00:05:55,840 --> 00:05:57,560
If any of them ever want to come...

77
00:06:08,240 --> 00:06:09,560
they'll kill you.

78
00:06:24,360 --> 00:06:25,840
(SPOON TINKLES)

79
00:06:37,760 --> 00:06:38,920
(SPACECRAFT APPROACHING)

80
00:06:54,760 --> 00:06:55,880
GASTRON ON PA: Attention.

81
00:06:55,960 --> 00:06:58,560
Will all non-military personnel
step away from the Doctor.

82
00:07:03,800 --> 00:07:05,320
I repeat,

83
00:07:05,400 --> 00:07:08,720
all non-military personnel,
please step away from the Doctor.

84
00:07:10,080 --> 00:07:11,680
At least move the children away.

85
00:07:14,400 --> 00:07:17,520
Doctor, you lay down
any weapons on your person

86
00:07:17,600 --> 00:07:19,480
and accompany us to the Capitol.

87
00:07:42,120 --> 00:07:44,120
Doctor, you will
accompany us to the Capitol.

88
00:08:03,040 --> 00:08:04,320
Doctor?

89
00:08:07,680 --> 00:08:09,120
Come back.

90
00:08:09,200 --> 00:08:10,920
You will come back, immediately.

91
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:13,800
That is an order.
And this is a military vehicle.

92
00:08:21,280 --> 00:08:22,760
What's his plan?

93
00:08:23,240 --> 00:08:25,280
I think he's finishing his soup.

94
00:08:27,320 --> 00:08:29,360
-Suggestion, sir.
-Mmm.

95
00:08:29,440 --> 00:08:31,600
GENERAL: We could talk to him.

96
00:08:31,680 --> 00:08:34,120
PRESIDENT: Words are his weapons.

97
00:08:34,200 --> 00:08:36,840
GENERAL: When did they stop being ours?

98
00:08:43,240 --> 00:08:44,360
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

99
00:09:08,480 --> 00:09:10,680
Welcome home, sir.

100
00:09:10,800 --> 00:09:13,720
As commander of the
armed forces of Gallifrey,

101
00:09:13,800 --> 00:09:17,000
I bring you the greetings
of the High Council.

102
00:09:23,400 --> 00:09:26,120
Who the hell does he think he is?

103
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:27,680
The man who won the Time War, sir.

104
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:34,600
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

105
00:09:52,480 --> 00:09:53,800
(DOOR SLAMS SHUT)

106
00:09:55,240 --> 00:09:56,720
What is he doing?

107
00:10:02,840 --> 00:10:04,320
What does he want?

108
00:10:05,600 --> 00:10:06,920
Revenge?

109
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:10,320
The Doctor does not blame Gallifrey
for the horrors of the Time War.

110
00:10:10,840 --> 00:10:12,720
I should hope not.

111
00:10:12,800 --> 00:10:14,680
He just blames you.

112
00:10:21,720 --> 00:10:22,720
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

113
00:10:23,720 --> 00:10:25,520
(BREATHING SHAKILY)

114
00:11:25,680 --> 00:11:27,240
Get off my planet.

115
00:11:29,440 --> 00:11:30,920
We needed to know.

116
00:11:32,320 --> 00:11:34,720
You have information about the Hybrid,

117
00:11:34,800 --> 00:11:37,040
a danger to all of us.

118
00:11:37,120 --> 00:11:39,640
If you told us what you knew,
you could have walked out of there.

119
00:11:39,720 --> 00:11:41,560
Get off my planet.

120
00:11:44,680 --> 00:11:47,320
You have nothing, Doctor. Nothing!

121
00:11:48,680 --> 00:11:50,720
Do you know what I have out here,

122
00:11:50,800 --> 00:11:54,080
in the dry lands,
where there's nobody who matters?

123
00:11:54,960 --> 00:11:56,880
No witnesses.

124
00:11:58,520 --> 00:12:00,000
Me, too.

125
00:12:02,040 --> 00:12:03,080
Take aim!

126
00:12:04,560 --> 00:12:05,920
Aim at the Doctor.

127
00:12:08,800 --> 00:12:11,400
-Fire on my command.
-Sir?

128
00:12:11,480 --> 00:12:14,400
PRESIDENT: Step forward and take aim!

129
00:12:14,480 --> 00:12:16,080
What's the matter with you?

130
00:12:16,160 --> 00:12:19,880
Lord President, he's a war hero.

131
00:12:19,960 --> 00:12:21,560
Some of these men served with him.

132
00:12:21,640 --> 00:12:23,120
These men serve me!

133
00:12:24,840 --> 00:12:25,920
All of you!

134
00:12:26,800 --> 00:12:28,760
(GUNS POWERING UP)

135
00:12:30,320 --> 00:12:32,160
On my command.

136
00:12:48,920 --> 00:12:50,400
Fire!

137
00:12:55,120 --> 00:12:56,240
DOCTOR: Could I have a lemonade?

138
00:12:57,800 --> 00:13:00,240
Oh. You like a cliffhanger, don't you?

139
00:13:03,400 --> 00:13:05,600
So, you went back to your hometown.

140
00:13:05,680 --> 00:13:06,920
Something like that.

141
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:08,560
Glasgow?

142
00:13:08,640 --> 00:13:10,000
Uh... Well, sort of Glasgow.

143
00:13:10,080 --> 00:13:11,720
Space Glasgow.

144
00:13:11,800 --> 00:13:13,480
And there's this gang boss
and he wanted to kill you?

145
00:13:14,720 --> 00:13:16,280
Wanted to. Yeah.

146
00:13:33,360 --> 00:13:34,840
You missed.

147
00:13:36,440 --> 00:13:40,200
All of you. Every single one of you.
How is that possible?

148
00:13:40,920 --> 00:13:42,080
What is it?

149
00:13:42,680 --> 00:13:45,600
Is the firing squad afraid
of the unarmed man?

150
00:13:48,120 --> 00:13:49,600
You, explain.

151
00:13:51,400 --> 00:13:53,560
There was a saying, sir,
in the Time War.

152
00:13:53,640 --> 00:13:54,640
A saying?

153
00:13:55,480 --> 00:13:58,080
GASTRON: First thing you notice
about the Doctor of War

154
00:13:59,240 --> 00:14:00,480
is he's unarmed.

155
00:14:01,520 --> 00:14:03,400
For many, it's also the last.

156
00:14:27,440 --> 00:14:28,880
I was at Skull Moon, sir.

157
00:14:32,520 --> 00:14:34,400
Is this a story
or did this really happen?

158
00:14:34,480 --> 00:14:37,120
Every story I ever told really happened.

159
00:14:38,680 --> 00:14:40,720
Stories

160
00:14:40,800 --> 00:14:42,720
are where memories go
when they're forgotten.

161
00:14:50,520 --> 00:14:53,160
Not one more of you moves.
That is an order.

162
00:14:54,280 --> 00:14:56,800
A direct order of your president!

163
00:15:00,960 --> 00:15:02,960
You leave me no choice.

164
00:15:04,880 --> 00:15:08,560
How many regenerations did we grant you?

165
00:15:08,640 --> 00:15:11,480
-I've got all night.
-(SPACECRAFTS APPROACHING)

166
00:15:14,480 --> 00:15:17,320
Excellent, General,
you sent for reinforcements.

167
00:15:17,400 --> 00:15:18,560
DOCTOR: No, he didn't.

168
00:15:21,800 --> 00:15:23,160
I did.

169
00:15:34,320 --> 00:15:38,280
I am Rassilon, the redeemer.

170
00:15:40,360 --> 00:15:42,280
Rassilon, the resurrected.

171
00:15:42,960 --> 00:15:45,680
Gallifrey is mine!

172
00:15:47,600 --> 00:15:51,240
Lord President, with respect,

173
00:15:52,320 --> 00:15:54,160
get off his planet.

174
00:16:14,200 --> 00:16:15,960
GENERAL: Gallifrey is
currently positioned

175
00:16:16,080 --> 00:16:20,240
at the extreme end of the time continuum
for its own protection.

176
00:16:21,440 --> 00:16:24,480
We're the end of the Universe,
give or take a star system.

177
00:16:24,560 --> 00:16:27,760
I know. I came the long way around.

178
00:16:29,720 --> 00:16:32,240
The President may not
find anywhere to go.

179
00:16:35,760 --> 00:16:37,720
He's not the president any more.

180
00:16:38,400 --> 00:16:40,920
He was a good man once.

181
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:43,720
Isn't this going a little far?

182
00:16:43,800 --> 00:16:46,000
Oh, I've barely started.

183
00:16:46,880 --> 00:16:49,560
Tell the High Council
they're on the next shuttle.

184
00:17:05,600 --> 00:17:09,240
OHILA: I thought I'd
find you down here. Old times.

185
00:17:12,760 --> 00:17:14,080
You're a long way from Karn.

186
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:18,040
At the end of everything, one must
expect the company of immortals.

187
00:17:19,080 --> 00:17:20,560
Do you know what they did to me?

188
00:17:21,600 --> 00:17:24,000
Confession dial is a ritual act
of purification.

189
00:17:24,080 --> 00:17:27,360
It allows a dying Time Lord
to face his demons and make his peace,

190
00:17:27,760 --> 00:17:31,200
before his mind
is uploaded to the Matrix.

191
00:17:31,280 --> 00:17:34,320
It was never intended
as a torture chamber for the living!

192
00:17:34,400 --> 00:17:38,160
Rassilon grew concerned about
the coming of the Hybrid.

193
00:17:38,240 --> 00:17:39,440
Afraid.

194
00:17:39,520 --> 00:17:41,960
You were entrapped
and imprisoned at his command.

195
00:17:42,520 --> 00:17:45,440
-And look at him now.
-Why did you banish him?

196
00:17:45,760 --> 00:17:48,600
Was it punishment,
or for your own protection?

197
00:17:49,040 --> 00:17:52,920
Were you just being cruel
or just being cowardly?

198
00:17:53,560 --> 00:17:55,320
Let's see, shall we?

199
00:17:56,920 --> 00:17:59,840
If you wanted to know about the Hybrid,
why didn't you just ask me?

200
00:17:59,920 --> 00:18:02,040
If the Hybrid is a threat
to the people of this world,

201
00:18:02,120 --> 00:18:03,520
why don't you just tell us?

202
00:18:04,280 --> 00:18:05,320
What do you know already?

203
00:18:07,480 --> 00:18:08,960
-The Hybrid is a legendary...
-No.

204
00:18:11,120 --> 00:18:15,080
The Hybrid is a creature thought to be
crossbred from two warrior races.

205
00:18:15,160 --> 00:18:16,800
Which races?

206
00:18:16,880 --> 00:18:19,080
The Daleks and the Time Lords.
It is supposed...

207
00:18:19,160 --> 00:18:20,880
Oh, it must be well hard then.

208
00:18:20,960 --> 00:18:24,280
Unstoppable, according to the stories.

209
00:18:24,360 --> 00:18:27,320
If they're just stories,
why are you so worried?

210
00:18:27,400 --> 00:18:29,640
Some Matrix prophecies suggest...

211
00:18:29,720 --> 00:18:31,200
No.

212
00:18:33,720 --> 00:18:35,200
Many prophecies suggest...

213
00:18:35,280 --> 00:18:36,760
No.

214
00:18:39,920 --> 00:18:45,640
All Matrix prophecies concur
that this creature will one day

215
00:18:45,720 --> 00:18:47,920
stand in the ruins of Gallifrey.

216
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:49,960
It will unravel the web of time

217
00:18:50,040 --> 00:18:53,520
and destroy a billion billion
hearts to heal his own.

218
00:18:53,600 --> 00:18:54,880
What colour is it?

219
00:18:56,680 --> 00:18:57,760
I don't know.

220
00:18:57,840 --> 00:19:00,400
These prophecies, they never tell
you anything useful, do they?

221
00:19:00,480 --> 00:19:02,280
This is no time to play the fool.

222
00:19:02,360 --> 00:19:04,480
It's the end of the Universe,
it's the only time I've got!

223
00:19:04,960 --> 00:19:06,640
And you want me to keep you all safe?

224
00:19:07,040 --> 00:19:10,080
-Can you?
-I'll need help, obviously.

225
00:19:10,160 --> 00:19:11,520
Gallifrey is at your command.

226
00:19:11,600 --> 00:19:13,920
Well, not from you lot.
No, you'd cramp my style.

227
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:15,480
Look at your hats.

228
00:19:16,880 --> 00:19:19,400
I'm going to need the use
of an extraction chamber

229
00:19:19,480 --> 00:19:22,720
to talk to an old friend.

230
00:19:32,240 --> 00:19:33,720
(RAVEN CROWING)

231
00:19:33,800 --> 00:19:35,080
(WHISPERS) Let me be brave.

232
00:19:37,080 --> 00:19:38,560
(THUD)

233
00:19:44,960 --> 00:19:46,520
(EXHALES SHARPLY)

234
00:19:52,760 --> 00:19:55,720
This way. I can save you.

235
00:20:18,360 --> 00:20:19,640
-Doctor?
-DOCTOR: Yeah.

236
00:20:19,720 --> 00:20:21,960
Where am I? Is this the Tardis?

237
00:20:22,040 --> 00:20:25,000
DOCTOR: No, this is a planet.
CLARA: What planet?

238
00:20:25,080 --> 00:20:27,800
-Basically, my place.
-I was about to die.

239
00:20:27,880 --> 00:20:29,520
I should be dead.

240
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:31,480
DOCTOR: Forget about that.
It doesn't matter.

241
00:20:31,560 --> 00:20:33,040
-Hang on. Your place?
-Yeah.

242
00:20:33,120 --> 00:20:34,440
-What do you mean your place?
-My place.

243
00:20:34,520 --> 00:20:35,960
-CLARA: You don't mean...
-Yeah.

244
00:20:36,400 --> 00:20:37,400
Gallifrey.

245
00:20:37,840 --> 00:20:39,320
Gallifrey.

246
00:20:40,240 --> 00:20:43,000
Okay. Uh... Hang on. Wait. What?

247
00:20:43,080 --> 00:20:44,960
What? Did I miss something?

248
00:20:45,040 --> 00:20:46,720
Well, we're several billion
years in the future

249
00:20:46,800 --> 00:20:48,160
and the universe is pretty much over,

250
00:20:48,240 --> 00:20:49,240
so, yeah, quite a lot.

251
00:20:49,320 --> 00:20:51,520
GENERAL: Young lady. Miss Oswald,

252
00:20:51,600 --> 00:20:53,680
I'm afraid we only have
a very few minutes with you.

253
00:20:56,960 --> 00:20:58,240
Who's he?

254
00:20:58,320 --> 00:21:00,040
According to the Doctor,
you can tell us something

255
00:21:00,120 --> 00:21:01,840
about the creature known as the Hybrid.

256
00:21:01,920 --> 00:21:03,680
Ah. Ooh.

257
00:21:03,760 --> 00:21:05,600
Well, that's weird.
What's wrong with my ears?

258
00:21:05,680 --> 00:21:06,800
-DOCTOR: Nothing.
-Ooh.

259
00:21:06,880 --> 00:21:08,600
It's weird. Everything sounds wrong.

260
00:21:08,680 --> 00:21:10,160
-DOCTOR: It's a side effect.
-I can hear you.

261
00:21:10,240 --> 00:21:11,280
-I can hear you fine.
-DOCTOR: Uh-huh.

262
00:21:11,360 --> 00:21:13,240
But I don't know. It's like, um...

263
00:21:13,600 --> 00:21:15,080
It's like something's missing.

264
00:21:15,160 --> 00:21:17,720
Doctor, we have to tell her.
We always tell them.

265
00:21:17,800 --> 00:21:20,680
Tell me what?
What's he talking about? Doctor?

266
00:21:26,520 --> 00:21:28,000
Doctor, what's going on?

267
00:21:29,360 --> 00:21:30,560
DOCTOR: Clara, there's a sound

268
00:21:30,640 --> 00:21:32,400
you've been living with
every day of your life,

269
00:21:32,480 --> 00:21:34,360
that you've learnt not to hear.

270
00:21:36,040 --> 00:21:37,080
What sound?

271
00:21:38,040 --> 00:21:39,760
What's wrong? Just tell me.

272
00:21:40,440 --> 00:21:41,720
Doctor, what sound?

273
00:21:41,800 --> 00:21:42,960
Your heartbeat.

274
00:21:46,240 --> 00:21:48,800
Your physical processes
have been time looped.

275
00:21:50,560 --> 00:21:54,240
Frozen between one heartbeat
and the next.

276
00:21:56,120 --> 00:21:57,600
Even your breathing is just a habit.

277
00:21:58,880 --> 00:22:00,360
You don't need it.

278
00:22:04,160 --> 00:22:07,000
If I'm frozen, how can I...

279
00:22:07,080 --> 00:22:08,560
How can I be walking about?

280
00:22:08,880 --> 00:22:11,120
Because the Time Lords are very clever.

281
00:22:11,200 --> 00:22:13,560
-It doesn't matter...
-Yes, it matters to me.

282
00:22:13,640 --> 00:22:15,800
Doctor, we have to explain.

283
00:22:15,880 --> 00:22:17,040
Doctor, what is going on?

284
00:22:17,120 --> 00:22:19,160
GENERAL: Although you are
currently conscious and aware,

285
00:22:19,240 --> 00:22:22,240
in fact, you died billions of years ago.

286
00:22:22,680 --> 00:22:23,840
Doctor?

287
00:22:24,280 --> 00:22:27,760
We have extracted you at the
very end of your time stream

288
00:22:27,840 --> 00:22:29,320
to request your help.

289
00:22:29,400 --> 00:22:33,360
Once we're finished here, you'll be
returned to your final moments.

290
00:22:33,440 --> 00:22:37,040
Your death is an
established historical event

291
00:22:37,160 --> 00:22:39,560
and cannot be altered. I'm sorry.

292
00:22:39,640 --> 00:22:41,120
Doctor, will you just talk to me?

293
00:22:41,240 --> 00:22:42,440
I'll try not to break your jaw.

294
00:22:42,560 --> 00:22:44,480
-My jaw?
-I wasn't talking to you.

295
00:22:44,560 --> 00:22:46,040
(GRUNTS)

296
00:22:48,800 --> 00:22:51,080
Doctor, you can't do this.
You know you can't.

297
00:22:51,160 --> 00:22:52,640
No, General, I don't know that.

298
00:22:52,880 --> 00:22:55,960
Everybody, stay exactly where you are.

299
00:22:56,040 --> 00:22:57,240
No moving about.

300
00:22:57,320 --> 00:22:58,920
On pain of death, no one take a selfie.

301
00:22:59,360 --> 00:23:00,840
These people are unarmed.

302
00:23:00,920 --> 00:23:02,400
So are you.

303
00:23:03,200 --> 00:23:05,200
Doctor, I will not let you leave here.

304
00:23:05,280 --> 00:23:09,320
That's the sidearm
of the president's personal security.

305
00:23:09,880 --> 00:23:11,240
There isn't a stun setting.

306
00:23:12,440 --> 00:23:14,560
I will not let Clara die.

307
00:23:14,640 --> 00:23:18,440
She's been dead
for half the lifetime of the universe.

308
00:23:18,520 --> 00:23:21,400
If you try to change that,
you could fracture time itself.

309
00:23:22,480 --> 00:23:25,760
Doctor, Lord President,
are you really gonna take that risk?

310
00:23:29,840 --> 00:23:30,880
Doctor.

311
00:23:34,480 --> 00:23:35,960
Please.

312
00:23:38,680 --> 00:23:39,720
I don't want this.

313
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:44,680
Put it down, please.

314
00:23:44,760 --> 00:23:45,880
Regeneration.

315
00:23:48,920 --> 00:23:50,120
Death.

316
00:23:51,080 --> 00:23:52,120
Good luck.

317
00:23:53,600 --> 00:23:55,080
-You too, sir.
-(GUNSHOT)

318
00:23:56,000 --> 00:23:57,360
I want a neural block.

319
00:23:58,120 --> 00:23:59,960
Human compatible. Quickly, come on.

320
00:24:01,520 --> 00:24:03,000
Come on. Quick!

321
00:24:04,280 --> 00:24:06,880
This Clara person,
you must really like her.

322
00:24:07,880 --> 00:24:09,800
Why do you say that?

323
00:24:09,880 --> 00:24:10,920
You killed a man.

324
00:24:12,120 --> 00:24:13,600
You don't seem the type.

325
00:24:14,320 --> 00:24:17,840
CLARA: You killed that man.
You shot him. He's dead.

326
00:24:17,920 --> 00:24:19,400
-DOCTOR: It was him or you.
-I don't care!

327
00:24:20,160 --> 00:24:23,400
Yeah? Well, the difference is,
when you die, you stay dead.

328
00:24:23,480 --> 00:24:24,960
So does he.

329
00:24:25,080 --> 00:24:28,000
We're on Gallifrey.
Death is Time Lord for man flu.

330
00:24:28,080 --> 00:24:30,720
Med Team to Sector 52,
extraction chamber seven.

331
00:24:30,800 --> 00:24:32,280
Regeneration in progress.

332
00:24:38,720 --> 00:24:40,040
Are you all right, sir?

333
00:24:43,280 --> 00:24:45,200
(STUTTERS) Uh, sorry, ma'am.

334
00:24:46,880 --> 00:24:48,360
(GRUNTS)

335
00:24:49,320 --> 00:24:50,800
Back to normal, am I?

336
00:24:51,480 --> 00:24:54,360
The only time I've been a man,
that last body.

337
00:24:54,440 --> 00:24:56,800
Dear Lord, how do you
cope with all that ego?

338
00:24:56,880 --> 00:24:58,320
Ma'am, where's the Doctor?

339
00:24:58,400 --> 00:25:01,520
The Cloisters. Where else would he run?

340
00:25:01,880 --> 00:25:03,960
Except into the greatest
danger on Gallifrey.

341
00:25:04,600 --> 00:25:06,600
The hell of the Time Lords.

342
00:25:07,000 --> 00:25:09,880
I thought you said Gallifrey was frozen
in another dimension.

343
00:25:10,040 --> 00:25:12,000
Well, they must have unfrozen it
and come back.

344
00:25:12,240 --> 00:25:13,360
CLARA: How?

345
00:25:13,440 --> 00:25:14,840
I didn't ask.
It'd make them feel clever.

346
00:25:19,080 --> 00:25:21,160
-Happy?
-No.

347
00:25:22,120 --> 00:25:24,640
Tell me what a neural block is.

348
00:25:24,720 --> 00:25:26,200
DOCTOR: Never mind.

349
00:25:26,720 --> 00:25:28,080
This way.

350
00:25:28,160 --> 00:25:30,160
CLARA: What did you mean,
human compatible?

351
00:25:30,240 --> 00:25:33,280
So, what was it, the thing you took?

352
00:25:33,360 --> 00:25:35,760
There was only one way
to keep Clara safe.

353
00:25:36,880 --> 00:25:38,680
I had to wipe some of her memory.

354
00:25:39,880 --> 00:25:41,240
Of what?

355
00:25:42,120 --> 00:25:43,360
Of me.

356
00:25:50,640 --> 00:25:53,320
The Cloister Wraiths.
Sliders, we used to call them.

357
00:25:53,960 --> 00:25:55,440
They guard the Matrix.

358
00:25:55,560 --> 00:25:56,920
-We're safe here.
-Why?

359
00:25:57,720 --> 00:26:00,000
They only attack
if you make any attempt to leave.

360
00:26:00,080 --> 00:26:01,560
How long are we planning to stay?

361
00:26:02,000 --> 00:26:03,480
Or actually, if you try to stay.

362
00:26:06,640 --> 00:26:08,920
You realise how well that
conversation went, right?

363
00:26:09,000 --> 00:26:10,600
I'm starting to, yeah, a bit.

364
00:26:14,600 --> 00:26:17,040
(EERIE HOWLING)

365
00:26:22,160 --> 00:26:24,120
FEMALE GENERAL: We need to block
every exit from the Cloisters.

366
00:26:24,200 --> 00:26:27,320
Every available man.
I need that place surrounded.

367
00:26:27,400 --> 00:26:29,480
No one's ever made it
back out of the Cloisters.

368
00:26:29,560 --> 00:26:31,560
No quite no one.

369
00:26:31,640 --> 00:26:33,160
DOCTOR: This way, I'm fairly sure.

370
00:26:33,240 --> 00:26:34,840
According to the stories,
there's a secret way out.

371
00:26:34,920 --> 00:26:37,240
If you find it, the Sliders let you go.

372
00:26:37,320 --> 00:26:41,600
DALEK: Exterminate.

373
00:26:42,760 --> 00:26:46,720
It's okay. It's okay. Look at it.

374
00:26:46,800 --> 00:26:51,080
Exterminate me.

375
00:26:51,160 --> 00:26:52,400
Is it trapped?

376
00:26:52,480 --> 00:26:54,840
DOCTOR: Don't worry,
it's been neutralised.

377
00:26:55,600 --> 00:26:57,280
Those aren't vines.

378
00:26:57,360 --> 00:27:01,360
In your terms, they are fibre optic
cables, they're alive and growing.

379
00:27:01,720 --> 00:27:04,040
We're inside the
biggest database in history.

380
00:27:04,120 --> 00:27:06,000
Sometimes, people are
stupid enough to break in.

381
00:27:06,080 --> 00:27:07,080
And?

382
00:27:08,560 --> 00:27:11,160
It's a database. They get filed.

383
00:27:11,240 --> 00:27:16,800
Exterminate...

384
00:27:18,040 --> 00:27:19,040
---177€.

385
00:27:19,120 --> 00:27:20,960
Probably left over
from the Cloister Wars.

386
00:27:22,040 --> 00:27:23,520
There's nothing we can do.

387
00:27:24,160 --> 00:27:25,200
Come on.

388
00:27:25,280 --> 00:27:27,800
Exterminate me!/

389
00:27:27,880 --> 00:27:31,600
Exterminate me!/

390
00:27:32,280 --> 00:27:34,480
Exterminate me!/

391
00:27:34,600 --> 00:27:36,080
(CLARA GASPS)

392
00:27:37,120 --> 00:27:41,160
Exterminate me!/

393
00:28:01,560 --> 00:28:02,800
Keep away from them.

394
00:28:04,240 --> 00:28:05,960
The Matrix can use them as a defence.

395
00:28:06,040 --> 00:28:08,200
It means the secret exit must be close.

396
00:28:13,280 --> 00:28:15,560
-What's to defend in a crypt?
-It's not just a crypt.

397
00:28:15,640 --> 00:28:16,880
It's more like a stone circuit board.

398
00:28:17,760 --> 00:28:19,320
This is the Matrix database.

399
00:28:19,400 --> 00:28:22,480
CLARA: Database?
What do you mean, database?

400
00:28:25,160 --> 00:28:26,640
- (WHISPERS) Oh.
-Oh?

401
00:28:27,160 --> 00:28:28,640
-Oh.
-Oh?

402
00:28:30,040 --> 00:28:31,520
Oh.

403
00:28:31,680 --> 00:28:33,800
Looks like the primary service hatch.

404
00:28:33,880 --> 00:28:35,800
-Just have to work out the key.
-Oh.

405
00:28:38,160 --> 00:28:42,560
When Time Lords die, their minds are
uploaded to a thing called the Matrix.

406
00:28:42,920 --> 00:28:45,360
This structure,
it's like a living computer.

407
00:28:45,840 --> 00:28:49,200
It can predict the future.
Generate prophecies out of algorithms.

408
00:28:50,000 --> 00:28:51,680
Ring the Cloister bells

409
00:28:51,760 --> 00:28:53,360
in the event of impending catastrophe.

410
00:28:56,480 --> 00:29:00,880
The Sliders, they're just like
the guard dogs, the firewall.

411
00:29:01,920 --> 00:29:03,400
They're projections from
inside the Matrix itself.

412
00:29:04,080 --> 00:29:08,480
The dead manning the battlements.

413
00:29:08,560 --> 00:29:10,400
Was I supposed to
understand any of that?

414
00:29:10,800 --> 00:29:12,720
The Time Lords have got a big computer

415
00:29:12,800 --> 00:29:15,360
made of ghosts in a crypt
guarded by more ghosts.

416
00:29:16,120 --> 00:29:17,760
-Didn't hurt, did it?
-Tiny bit.

417
00:29:25,760 --> 00:29:28,400
Why would a computer need to protect
itself from the people who made it?

418
00:29:28,480 --> 00:29:30,120
DOCTOR: All computers
do that in the end.

419
00:29:30,200 --> 00:29:33,320
You wait till the internet starts.
Oh, that was a war.

420
00:29:36,120 --> 00:29:37,560
GASTRON: They don't seem to be moving.

421
00:29:37,640 --> 00:29:38,960
They're by lift shaft seven.

422
00:29:40,680 --> 00:29:41,720
Keep monitoring.

423
00:29:46,360 --> 00:29:48,080
Long time ago,
there was a student at the academy.

424
00:29:48,160 --> 00:29:49,560
He'd got in here.

425
00:29:49,640 --> 00:29:51,120
Disappeared for four days.

426
00:29:52,480 --> 00:29:54,720
Showed up in a completely
different part of the city.

427
00:29:55,400 --> 00:29:58,160
He said the Sliders talked to him.

428
00:29:58,240 --> 00:30:00,640
They showed him the secret passage out.

429
00:30:00,720 --> 00:30:02,360
We just need the code.

430
00:30:02,440 --> 00:30:04,440
What, and the kid told you the secret?

431
00:30:04,520 --> 00:30:07,520
Ah, no. He didn't tell anyone anything.
He went completely mad.

432
00:30:07,600 --> 00:30:09,240
Never right in the head again,
so they say.

433
00:30:09,320 --> 00:30:10,720
Okay, that's encouraging.

434
00:30:10,800 --> 00:30:12,520
The last I heard,

435
00:30:12,600 --> 00:30:15,200
he stole the moon
and the President's wife.

436
00:30:18,520 --> 00:30:19,920
Was she, um...

437
00:30:20,000 --> 00:30:21,920
Was she nice, the President's wife?

438
00:30:22,000 --> 00:30:24,360
DOCTOR: Ah, well, that was a lie
put about by the Shabogans.

439
00:30:24,440 --> 00:30:26,160
-(BEEPING)
-It was the President's daughter.

440
00:30:26,240 --> 00:30:28,000
I didn't steal the moon. I lost...

441
00:30:29,960 --> 00:30:31,200
I'd know you anywhere.

442
00:30:33,920 --> 00:30:36,440
I was a completely different person
in those days.

443
00:30:36,520 --> 00:30:38,320
Eccentric. A bit mad!

444
00:30:38,400 --> 00:30:40,440
(CHUCKLES) Rude to people.

445
00:30:40,520 --> 00:30:42,320
-Look at me again.
-I'm sorry, what?

446
00:30:42,400 --> 00:30:45,280
In the eye, look at me. Just do it.

447
00:30:46,080 --> 00:30:47,440
What...

448
00:30:49,360 --> 00:30:50,640
What is it?

449
00:30:53,360 --> 00:30:55,120
How long has it been for you
since you last saw me?

450
00:30:55,200 --> 00:30:56,640
Oh... (MUMBLES)

451
00:30:57,120 --> 00:30:58,280
-Well, I'm not sure.
-How long?

452
00:31:00,440 --> 00:31:01,760
I was stuck in a place.

453
00:31:02,960 --> 00:31:04,280
-They...
-They?

454
00:31:04,360 --> 00:31:06,040
What... Who... Who are we talking about?

455
00:31:06,120 --> 00:31:08,040
They wanted something from me.
Information.

456
00:31:10,720 --> 00:31:12,080
It really doesn't matter.

457
00:31:17,320 --> 00:31:19,000
What happened to your coat?

458
00:31:19,080 --> 00:31:21,080
Velvety one? I liked that one. It was...

459
00:31:21,840 --> 00:31:22,840
It was very Doctor-ey...

460
00:31:22,920 --> 00:31:23,920
-I changed it.
-Why?

461
00:31:24,000 --> 00:31:25,640
Well, I can't be the Doctor
all the time.

462
00:31:25,720 --> 00:31:26,880
(BEEPING)

463
00:31:26,960 --> 00:31:29,720
I think I've almost got it.
I think this is it.

464
00:31:29,800 --> 00:31:31,120
Tell me what they did to you.

465
00:31:31,840 --> 00:31:33,640
Tell me what happened to the Doctor?

466
00:31:36,400 --> 00:31:37,480
We're here.

467
00:31:37,560 --> 00:31:39,720
Looks pretty quiet.

468
00:31:39,800 --> 00:31:41,680
He seems to be talking to her.

469
00:31:41,760 --> 00:31:43,800
Like he's telling her a story.

470
00:31:43,880 --> 00:31:45,520
You might want to have a look.

471
00:31:45,600 --> 00:31:47,760
Open up. We're going in.

472
00:31:47,840 --> 00:31:50,560
We'll stick to the perimeter.
No more than three paces from the lift.

473
00:31:50,640 --> 00:31:52,760
Do not enter the Cloisters.

474
00:31:52,840 --> 00:31:55,960
DOCTOR: ...twenty feet of pure diamond.
Harder than diamond.

475
00:31:57,480 --> 00:31:59,240
But you'll break through anything,
given time.

476
00:32:00,120 --> 00:32:01,200
CLARA: How much time?

477
00:32:01,280 --> 00:32:03,120
-FEMALE GENERAL: Miss Oswald.
-Stay back.

478
00:32:03,200 --> 00:32:05,360
I'm sorry. But we have to find a way...

479
00:32:05,440 --> 00:32:07,480
I said stay back!

480
00:32:14,920 --> 00:32:16,920
The Hybrid. What is it?

481
00:32:17,000 --> 00:32:18,680
What's so important
you would fight so long?

482
00:32:18,760 --> 00:32:20,120
It doesn't matter what the Hybrid is.

483
00:32:20,200 --> 00:32:22,280
It only matters that I
convinced them that I knew.

484
00:32:22,360 --> 00:32:23,760
Otherwise, they would have kicked me out

485
00:32:23,840 --> 00:32:25,240
and I'd have nothing left
to bargain with.

486
00:32:25,320 --> 00:32:27,720
-What were you bargain for?
-What do you think?

487
00:32:29,680 --> 00:32:30,840
(WHISPERS) You.

488
00:32:31,040 --> 00:32:33,240
I had to find a way to save you.

489
00:32:33,320 --> 00:32:34,560
I knew it had to be the Time Lords.

490
00:32:34,640 --> 00:32:36,520
They cost you your life
on Trap Street, Clara.

491
00:32:36,600 --> 00:32:38,560
And I was gonna make them
bring you back.

492
00:32:38,640 --> 00:32:40,480
I just had to hang on
in there for a bit.

493
00:32:41,520 --> 00:32:43,760
-How long?
-It was fine.

494
00:32:48,080 --> 00:32:49,240
One question,

495
00:32:49,320 --> 00:32:50,960
and you will answer.

496
00:32:51,040 --> 00:32:53,200
How long was the Doctor trapped
inside the confession dial?

497
00:32:53,280 --> 00:32:57,800
We think four-and-a-half billion years.

498
00:32:58,600 --> 00:33:00,440
FEMALE GENERAL:
He could have left anytime he wanted.

499
00:33:00,520 --> 00:33:02,120
He just had to say what he knew.

500
00:33:02,200 --> 00:33:03,880
The dial would have released him.

501
00:33:11,280 --> 00:33:12,880
(BEEPING)

502
00:33:19,640 --> 00:33:21,800
(SOFTLY) Four-and-a-half billion years?

503
00:33:23,400 --> 00:33:25,600
-If she says so.
-No.

504
00:33:27,960 --> 00:33:29,640
Why would you even do that?

505
00:33:30,640 --> 00:33:31,800
I was dead.

506
00:33:32,480 --> 00:33:34,400
I was dead and gone. Why?

507
00:33:34,480 --> 00:33:37,240
Why would you even
do that to yourself? (SIGHS)

508
00:33:40,560 --> 00:33:41,960
I had a duty of care.

509
00:33:44,480 --> 00:33:46,360
Listen, I'm nearly through here.

510
00:33:46,440 --> 00:33:47,480
(BEEPING)

511
00:33:48,640 --> 00:33:51,560
If I'm right, there should be
a service duct under here.

512
00:33:51,640 --> 00:33:53,520
We'll be able to get
to the Old Workshops.

513
00:33:53,600 --> 00:33:55,200
They'll have Tardises.

514
00:33:55,440 --> 00:33:57,560
-(SNIFFS) Okay, listen.
-(HATCH DOOR OPENS)

515
00:33:58,240 --> 00:33:59,560
I have something I need to say.

516
00:33:59,640 --> 00:34:02,280
-We do not have time.
-No, my time...

517
00:34:04,440 --> 00:34:07,240
My time is up, Doctor.

518
00:34:07,320 --> 00:34:10,040
Between one heartbeat and the last
is all the time I have.

519
00:34:12,680 --> 00:34:14,360
People like me and you,

520
00:34:15,360 --> 00:34:17,040
we should say things to one another.

521
00:34:17,640 --> 00:34:19,360
CLARA: And I'm gonna say them now.

522
00:34:41,880 --> 00:34:43,480
You're monsters.

523
00:34:44,240 --> 00:34:45,680
Here you are.

524
00:34:45,760 --> 00:34:47,560
Hiding away at the end of time.

525
00:34:47,640 --> 00:34:49,160
Do you even know why?

526
00:34:50,280 --> 00:34:51,760
Because you are hated.

527
00:34:53,120 --> 00:34:57,480
You are hated!

528
00:34:58,560 --> 00:35:00,120
By everybody.

529
00:35:00,200 --> 00:35:02,000
But by nobody more than me.

530
00:35:02,080 --> 00:35:03,840
-What did you say to him?
-(DOOR BEEPING)

531
00:35:03,920 --> 00:35:05,600
Oh, nothing I'm gonna tell you.

532
00:35:05,680 --> 00:35:07,280
Or anybody else.

533
00:35:08,200 --> 00:35:10,280
Except maybe this one part.

534
00:35:10,360 --> 00:35:11,880
I said...

535
00:35:15,600 --> 00:35:17,240
"Don't worry, Doctor.

536
00:35:18,880 --> 00:35:20,360
"They'll all be looking at me."

537
00:35:23,760 --> 00:35:26,200
You need to tell us what
the Doctor is going to do now.

538
00:35:26,280 --> 00:35:27,800
You really are thick, aren't you?

539
00:35:28,760 --> 00:35:30,960
The Doctor is back on Gallifrey.

540
00:35:31,040 --> 00:35:33,920
Took him four-and-a-half
billion years to get here.

541
00:35:35,240 --> 00:35:36,720
What do you think he's gonna do now?

542
00:35:36,800 --> 00:35:38,560
(WHOOSHING)

543
00:35:38,640 --> 00:35:41,640
Well, he's stealing a Tardis
and running away.

544
00:35:41,720 --> 00:35:43,520
Bye.

545
00:35:44,840 --> 00:35:46,200
CLARA: You were quick!

546
00:35:46,280 --> 00:35:48,040
Time machine, I backed up a bit.

547
00:35:48,120 --> 00:35:50,800
OHILA: Doctor. Doctor, face me!

548
00:35:50,880 --> 00:35:52,640
Doctor, can you hear me?

549
00:35:52,720 --> 00:35:55,240
Get out of that Tardis and face me, boy!

550
00:35:55,360 --> 00:35:57,240
-Boy?
-(BEEPING)

551
00:36:00,640 --> 00:36:02,080
OHILA: You have gone too far.

552
00:36:02,160 --> 00:36:04,920
You have broken every code
you ever lived by.

553
00:36:05,000 --> 00:36:08,440
After all this time,
after everything I've done,

554
00:36:08,520 --> 00:36:09,880
don't you think the universe
owes me this?

555
00:36:09,960 --> 00:36:11,000
Owes you what?

556
00:36:11,080 --> 00:36:12,760
All you're doing is giving her hope?

557
00:36:12,840 --> 00:36:14,200
Since when is hope a bad thing?

558
00:36:14,280 --> 00:36:18,160
Hope is a terrible thing
on the scaffold.

559
00:36:22,680 --> 00:36:24,240
(TARDIS WHOOSHING)

560
00:36:24,320 --> 00:36:25,680
(GRUNTS)

561
00:36:27,800 --> 00:36:29,080
FEMALE GENERAL: Where can he run?

562
00:36:29,160 --> 00:36:31,120
Where he always runs.

563
00:36:31,200 --> 00:36:32,360
Away.

564
00:36:34,080 --> 00:36:36,240
Just away.

565
00:36:38,680 --> 00:36:40,240
DOCTOR: What do you think
of the new wheels?

566
00:36:40,320 --> 00:36:42,080
-Basic.
-Classic. Look at the colour scheme.

567
00:36:42,200 --> 00:36:43,920
-(CHUCKLES) It's all white.
-Genius!

568
00:36:44,000 --> 00:36:45,880
(THUD)

569
00:36:46,080 --> 00:36:47,200
Check your heartbeat again.

570
00:36:48,840 --> 00:36:51,920
-I think that you'll find you have one.
-Yeah?

571
00:36:52,000 --> 00:36:54,880
It should've restarted when we broke
free of Gallifrey's time zone.

572
00:36:56,320 --> 00:36:57,800
You're alive!

573
00:36:57,880 --> 00:36:59,880
Now, we just have to shake off
the Time Lords.

574
00:36:59,960 --> 00:37:01,720
There's only place we can do that.

575
00:37:01,800 --> 00:37:03,720
What do say to lunch
followed by breakfast,

576
00:37:03,800 --> 00:37:05,640
because we're time travellers
and that's how we roll?

577
00:37:05,720 --> 00:37:07,840
Then cocktails with Moses.

578
00:37:07,920 --> 00:37:09,640
Then I'm going to invent
a flying submarine. Why?

579
00:37:09,720 --> 00:37:11,440
Because no one ever has,
and it's annoying!

580
00:37:12,200 --> 00:37:14,200
And maybe we should use this Tardis
to find my proper one.

581
00:37:14,280 --> 00:37:15,840
I need to change my shirt.

582
00:37:18,080 --> 00:37:19,080
Doctor.

583
00:37:20,040 --> 00:37:21,240
I still don't have a pulse.

584
00:37:21,840 --> 00:37:23,000
Oh, you just haven't found it yet.

585
00:37:23,080 --> 00:37:24,640
-Try again.
-I know how to take my pulse.

586
00:37:24,720 --> 00:37:27,240
-(SIGHS)
-Look, I know how to do it.

587
00:37:29,080 --> 00:37:30,200
See, no pulse, right?

588
00:37:31,400 --> 00:37:33,480
-Uh-huh.
-(GLASSES WHIRRING)

589
00:37:37,560 --> 00:37:40,200
Is it still there? Don't lie to me.

590
00:37:40,280 --> 00:37:42,440
Uh, maybe we just have to fly
a little bit further.

591
00:37:42,520 --> 00:37:44,560
Give it a bit more welly.

592
00:37:48,960 --> 00:37:50,320
They said, your lot...

593
00:37:50,760 --> 00:37:53,240
That if you save me, time would
fracture. What does that mean?

594
00:37:53,320 --> 00:37:55,920
Ah, they were just exaggerating.

595
00:37:56,000 --> 00:37:58,240
They exaggerate all the time.

596
00:37:58,320 --> 00:38:00,720
History will be fine.

597
00:38:00,800 --> 00:38:03,040
Time will heal. It always does.

598
00:38:03,120 --> 00:38:04,880
-Always?
-Yeah.

599
00:38:04,960 --> 00:38:07,680
It'll sort itself out.
It'll be all right.

600
00:38:07,760 --> 00:38:10,040
You'll have a heartbeat.
Or don't you trust me any more?

601
00:38:11,600 --> 00:38:13,440
No. Not when you're shouting.

602
00:38:21,440 --> 00:38:23,640
-Where are we going?
-Nowhere in space.

603
00:38:24,600 --> 00:38:25,960
Forward in time.

604
00:38:27,920 --> 00:38:30,720
We're going to the last hours
of the universe.

605
00:38:30,800 --> 00:38:34,400
We're going long past where
the Time Lords were hiding.

606
00:38:34,480 --> 00:38:36,040
Literally, to the end.

607
00:38:36,920 --> 00:38:39,440
They won't be able to track us there.

608
00:38:39,520 --> 00:38:41,160
We'll just be there for a minute.

609
00:38:41,240 --> 00:38:42,920
I just need to...

610
00:38:45,600 --> 00:38:47,600
I need to make an adjustment.

611
00:38:47,680 --> 00:38:49,000
To what?

612
00:38:49,080 --> 00:38:51,520
It's nothing, really. It's this...

613
00:38:51,600 --> 00:38:54,680
A neural block?
Human compatible, that's what you said.

614
00:39:00,440 --> 00:39:01,840
We don't have to stay here long.

615
00:39:02,280 --> 00:39:04,360
Uh, check your heartbeat again.

616
00:39:04,440 --> 00:39:07,160
Your timeline must have started by now.

617
00:39:08,120 --> 00:39:09,160
Pulse, yeah?

618
00:39:10,760 --> 00:39:12,360
You have a pulse, yes?

619
00:39:13,320 --> 00:39:15,600
Pulse? Let me do it.

620
00:39:15,680 --> 00:39:18,120
-I am checking it properly.
-This should work.

621
00:39:19,160 --> 00:39:20,520
This has got to work.

622
00:39:21,760 --> 00:39:24,080
CLARA: What if one last heartbeat
is all I've got.

623
00:39:25,640 --> 00:39:27,440
What if time isn't healing?

624
00:39:27,520 --> 00:39:29,600
What if the universe needs me to die?

625
00:39:29,680 --> 00:39:31,920
The universe is over!
It doesn't have a say any more!

626
00:39:32,000 --> 00:39:34,080
We're standing on the last ember.

627
00:39:34,160 --> 00:39:36,960
The last fragment
of everything that ever was.

628
00:39:37,040 --> 00:39:39,680
As of this moment,
I'm answerable to no one!

629
00:39:47,640 --> 00:39:48,920
(SIGHS)

630
00:39:49,000 --> 00:39:50,280
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

631
00:39:54,720 --> 00:39:56,320
How can there be anybody there?

632
00:39:56,400 --> 00:39:57,640
(KNOCKING CONTINUES)

633
00:39:57,720 --> 00:39:59,200
Four knocks.

634
00:40:00,800 --> 00:40:02,560
It's always four knocks.

635
00:40:03,920 --> 00:40:04,960
No.

636
00:40:06,200 --> 00:40:07,880
This one, I do alone.

637
00:40:07,960 --> 00:40:09,480
What's out there?

638
00:40:10,520 --> 00:40:11,880
Me.

639
00:40:14,560 --> 00:40:16,280
(WHIRRING)

640
00:40:28,520 --> 00:40:30,240
I told you once

641
00:40:31,920 --> 00:40:33,520
so long ago

642
00:40:36,600 --> 00:40:40,240
that the universe would become a very
small place when I'm angry with you.

643
00:40:42,800 --> 00:40:44,360
Small enough for you yet?

644
00:40:46,640 --> 00:40:48,200
Hello, me.

645
00:40:49,240 --> 00:40:50,960
You don't seem surprised to see me.

646
00:40:54,040 --> 00:40:55,440
DOCTOR: At the end of everything,
we should expect

647
00:40:55,520 --> 00:40:57,800
the company of immortals,
so I've been told.

648
00:40:59,000 --> 00:41:00,840
Even the other immortals are gone.

649
00:41:02,080 --> 00:41:03,320
It's just me.

650
00:41:04,680 --> 00:41:06,200
The one and only me.

651
00:41:06,760 --> 00:41:07,960
Finally, you earned the title.

652
00:41:08,040 --> 00:41:10,880
Sitting here in a reality bubble
at the end of time itself.

653
00:41:10,960 --> 00:41:12,400
How are you sustaining it, by the way?

654
00:41:13,360 --> 00:41:14,600
Brilliantly.

655
00:41:16,120 --> 00:41:17,760
I've been watching stars die.

656
00:41:19,440 --> 00:41:20,640
It was beautiful.

657
00:41:24,520 --> 00:41:25,840
No.

658
00:41:27,120 --> 00:41:28,360
It was sad.

659
00:41:28,440 --> 00:41:30,000
No.

660
00:41:30,080 --> 00:41:31,400
It was both.

661
00:41:32,360 --> 00:41:35,080
But that's not something
you would understand, is it?

662
00:41:36,440 --> 00:41:38,280
You don't like endings.

663
00:41:39,920 --> 00:41:41,520
She died, Doctor.

664
00:41:42,880 --> 00:41:45,920
Clara died billions of years ago.

665
00:41:46,000 --> 00:41:47,400
-You killed her.
-No.

666
00:41:47,480 --> 00:41:49,480
-You let it happen.
-No, I didn't.

667
00:41:49,560 --> 00:41:51,040
Neither did you.

668
00:41:51,120 --> 00:41:53,080
She did.

669
00:41:53,160 --> 00:41:55,160
She died for who she was
and for who she loved.

670
00:41:56,040 --> 00:41:58,240
She fell where she stood. It was sad.

671
00:41:58,640 --> 00:42:00,400
And it was beautiful.

672
00:42:02,160 --> 00:42:03,840
And it is over.

673
00:42:03,920 --> 00:42:06,320
We have no right to change who she was.

674
00:42:06,400 --> 00:42:07,800
-Ashildr.
-Me.

675
00:42:07,880 --> 00:42:09,240
Me, go to hell.

676
00:42:09,320 --> 00:42:11,960
By my calculations,
you've got about five minutes.

677
00:42:13,000 --> 00:42:14,840
You know why we run, Doctor?

678
00:42:14,920 --> 00:42:16,000
Because it's fun.

679
00:42:16,080 --> 00:42:18,360
Because we know
summer can't last forever.

680
00:42:19,160 --> 00:42:20,320
Of course it can.

681
00:42:20,400 --> 00:42:22,280
Of course it can.

682
00:42:22,960 --> 00:42:24,680
You just have to steal a time machine.

683
00:42:24,760 --> 00:42:25,920
The Hybrid.

684
00:42:28,440 --> 00:42:30,960
Five minutes to hell.
I think it's time to tell the truth.

685
00:42:31,040 --> 00:42:32,520
(BEEPING)

686
00:42:46,760 --> 00:42:47,920
Screen on.

687
00:42:48,000 --> 00:42:50,200
ASHILDR: You were barely
more than a child.

688
00:42:50,280 --> 00:42:52,200
You broke in here.

689
00:42:52,280 --> 00:42:54,240
And the Wraith spoke to you
about the Hybrid.

690
00:42:54,320 --> 00:42:56,080
Why did that story make you so scared?

691
00:42:56,160 --> 00:42:57,400
DOCTOR: I don't know.
I don't remember everything.

692
00:42:57,920 --> 00:42:59,440
(CHUCKLES) Sometimes you do.

693
00:43:00,320 --> 00:43:02,240
It's always the way with things
we'd rather forget.

694
00:43:02,320 --> 00:43:04,120
You remember now, though, don't you?

695
00:43:04,200 --> 00:43:06,920
Tell me, Doctor, who is the Hybrid?

696
00:43:07,000 --> 00:43:09,040
Who threatens all of time and space?

697
00:43:09,120 --> 00:43:11,240
Oh, that's easy. That's very, very easy.

698
00:43:11,320 --> 00:43:13,040
The Hybrid

699
00:43:14,080 --> 00:43:15,080
is you.

700
00:43:16,800 --> 00:43:19,760
ASHILDR: I'm human,
with a little bit of Mire inside me.

701
00:43:19,840 --> 00:43:22,120
The Hybrid is supposed to be
half Time Lord, half Dalek.

702
00:43:22,200 --> 00:43:23,480
DOCTOR: No, it isn't.

703
00:43:23,560 --> 00:43:26,640
The actual prophecy specifies
only two warrior races.

704
00:43:26,720 --> 00:43:29,160
The Daleks and the Time Lords
have made assumptions, of course.

705
00:43:29,240 --> 00:43:30,480
And they would.

706
00:43:30,560 --> 00:43:33,240
Humans and the Mire.

707
00:43:34,080 --> 00:43:36,200
Both warrior races, it fits perfectly.

708
00:43:37,520 --> 00:43:39,040
It's an interesting theory.

709
00:43:40,320 --> 00:43:41,520
Do you have a better one?

710
00:43:42,240 --> 00:43:44,400
By your own reasoning,

711
00:43:44,480 --> 00:43:48,160
why couldn't the Hybrid be
half Time Lord, half human?

712
00:43:51,600 --> 00:43:55,160
Tell me, Doctor, I've always wondered.
You're a Time Lord,

713
00:43:55,240 --> 00:43:57,160
you're a highborn Gallifreyan.

714
00:43:58,240 --> 00:44:00,640
Why is it you spend
so much time on Earth?

715
00:44:03,480 --> 00:44:05,640
That's your best theory? I'm the Hybrid?

716
00:44:05,720 --> 00:44:08,280
I've run away from Gallifrey
because I was afraid of myself?

717
00:44:08,360 --> 00:44:10,280
It doesn't make any sense.

718
00:44:10,360 --> 00:44:12,760
It makes perfect sense, and you know it.

719
00:44:13,920 --> 00:44:15,280
Am I right?

720
00:44:16,560 --> 00:44:17,880
Is it true?

721
00:44:17,960 --> 00:44:19,280
Does it matter?

722
00:44:22,080 --> 00:44:23,360
No.

723
00:44:25,320 --> 00:44:27,440
Because I have a better theory.

724
00:44:28,080 --> 00:44:29,360
Really?

725
00:44:29,440 --> 00:44:33,440
What if the Hybrid
wasn't one person, but two?

726
00:44:37,160 --> 00:44:38,880
-Two?
-A dangerous combination

727
00:44:39,480 --> 00:44:42,240
of a passionate and powerful Time Lord

728
00:44:42,320 --> 00:44:45,160
and a young woman
so very similar to him.

729
00:44:45,240 --> 00:44:48,720
Companions who are willing to
push each other to extremes.

730
00:44:48,800 --> 00:44:52,000
DOCTOR: She's my friend.
She's just my friend.

731
00:44:52,080 --> 00:44:53,600
ASHILDR: How did you meet her?

732
00:44:54,360 --> 00:44:55,520
Missy?

733
00:44:56,520 --> 00:44:57,800
Missy.

734
00:44:58,600 --> 00:45:01,160
Missy, the Master.

735
00:45:02,880 --> 00:45:04,480
The lover of chaos.

736
00:45:05,320 --> 00:45:07,000
Who wants you to love it, too.

737
00:45:07,080 --> 00:45:08,520
She's quite the matchmaker.

738
00:45:09,760 --> 00:45:11,280
Clara's my friend.

739
00:45:11,360 --> 00:45:12,560
I know.

740
00:45:13,800 --> 00:45:18,000
And you're willing to risk all of time
and space because you miss her.

741
00:45:19,200 --> 00:45:21,760
One wonders what the pair of you
will get up to next.

742
00:45:21,840 --> 00:45:24,040
Nothing. Nothing at all.

743
00:45:24,600 --> 00:45:26,680
I know I went too far.

744
00:45:26,760 --> 00:45:28,280
I get it.

745
00:45:28,360 --> 00:45:30,720
That's why I'm doing what I'm doing.

746
00:45:30,800 --> 00:45:32,040
And what would that be?

747
00:45:32,120 --> 00:45:33,280
I'm taking her back to Earth.

748
00:45:33,360 --> 00:45:35,800
Somewhere safe,
somewhere out of the way.

749
00:45:35,880 --> 00:45:38,800
I'm going to wipe her memory
of every last detail of me.

750
00:45:40,080 --> 00:45:42,080
It'll be like our friendship
never happened.

751
00:45:42,160 --> 00:45:44,000
ASHILDR: 7hat may not be what she wants.

752
00:45:44,080 --> 00:45:46,080
DOCTOR: I've done it before.

753
00:45:46,840 --> 00:45:48,800
Usually, I do it telepathically.

754
00:45:48,880 --> 00:45:51,040
But this time,
I've got something better.

755
00:45:53,400 --> 00:45:56,360
It's quite painless.

756
00:45:57,240 --> 00:45:59,000
Will you tell her
what you're going to do?

757
00:45:59,080 --> 00:46:01,520
-Of course.
-When?

758
00:46:02,160 --> 00:46:03,400
Now.

759
00:46:08,040 --> 00:46:10,240
-Screen off.
-(MONITOR BEEPING)

760
00:46:23,120 --> 00:46:24,440
You okay?

761
00:46:24,520 --> 00:46:26,000
CLARA: Yeah.

762
00:46:26,400 --> 00:46:28,920
Yeah, yeah. Just, you know, my pulse.

763
00:46:29,000 --> 00:46:30,800
Yeah, we'll fix that somehow, I promise.

764
00:46:30,880 --> 00:46:32,800
You remember Ashildr, of course.

765
00:46:32,880 --> 00:46:34,160
Yeah, sure.

766
00:46:35,880 --> 00:46:37,520
I thought you'd be
more surprised to see her?

767
00:46:40,560 --> 00:46:41,600
I was watching.

768
00:46:42,960 --> 00:46:44,440
On the monitor.

769
00:46:45,320 --> 00:46:47,160
(GASPS) No.

770
00:46:47,720 --> 00:46:50,760
Doctor, whatever you're about to do,
don't do it.

771
00:46:50,840 --> 00:46:52,120
It won't hurt, it'll be nothing.

772
00:46:52,200 --> 00:46:53,560
-You will just pass out for a moment.
-And then?

773
00:46:53,640 --> 00:46:56,240
-When you wake, you will be fine.
-But...

774
00:46:56,320 --> 00:46:58,160
-Clara, just listen to me.
-Just say it.

775
00:46:58,240 --> 00:47:00,920
Say it. Come on, tell me.

776
00:47:01,000 --> 00:47:02,920
When you wake up,
you will have forgotten me.

777
00:47:03,000 --> 00:47:04,560
You will have forgotten
we ever even met.

778
00:47:04,640 --> 00:47:05,800
And why would I want that?

779
00:47:05,880 --> 00:47:07,080
Because it's the only way.

780
00:47:07,160 --> 00:47:09,000
That stuff in your head,
the image of me,

781
00:47:09,080 --> 00:47:11,120
they could use it to find you.

782
00:47:11,200 --> 00:47:13,200
I, uh... I used these.

783
00:47:13,280 --> 00:47:14,520
-On what?
-That.

784
00:47:14,600 --> 00:47:16,480
-What did you do?
-What do you think?

785
00:47:16,560 --> 00:47:18,360
Ashildr's right, you see?
We're too alike.

786
00:47:18,440 --> 00:47:19,720
-Tell me what you did.
-What else?

787
00:47:19,800 --> 00:47:22,040
What else do you think I did?
I reversed the polarity.

788
00:47:22,120 --> 00:47:24,680
Push that button, Doctor,
it will go off in your own face.

789
00:47:24,760 --> 00:47:26,640
-Are you trying to trick me?
-What are you trying to do to me?

790
00:47:26,720 --> 00:47:28,800
-I'm trying to keep you safe.
-Why?

791
00:47:30,280 --> 00:47:32,080
Nobody's ever safe.

792
00:47:32,160 --> 00:47:33,880
I've never asked you for that, ever.

793
00:47:35,000 --> 00:47:36,760
These have been
the best years of my life.

794
00:47:36,840 --> 00:47:38,200
And they are mine.

795
00:47:40,240 --> 00:47:43,600
Tomorrow's promised to no one, Doctor,
but I insist upon my past,

796
00:47:43,680 --> 00:47:45,320
I am entitled to that.

797
00:47:47,360 --> 00:47:48,600
It's mine.

798
00:47:59,280 --> 00:48:01,600
DOCTOR: Oh, Clara Oswald.

799
00:48:04,800 --> 00:48:06,280
What am I doing?

800
00:48:11,760 --> 00:48:13,200
You're right.

801
00:48:15,040 --> 00:48:17,120
You're always...

802
00:48:17,200 --> 00:48:18,720
Always right.

803
00:48:21,880 --> 00:48:24,760
So what happens now? Eh?

804
00:48:25,360 --> 00:48:27,080
Me and you, what do we do now?

805
00:48:27,880 --> 00:48:29,760
I'm not sure you managed
to reverse the polarity.

806
00:48:29,840 --> 00:48:32,080
I'm not even sure that you can.

807
00:48:34,360 --> 00:48:35,640
It'll do something.

808
00:48:36,480 --> 00:48:37,520
To one of us.

809
00:48:38,320 --> 00:48:39,800
Better than flipping a coin.

810
00:48:41,160 --> 00:48:42,480
Doctor...

811
00:48:44,920 --> 00:48:46,960
You and me, together.

812
00:48:49,720 --> 00:48:51,240
Look how far I went.

813
00:48:52,320 --> 00:48:53,840
For fear of losing you.

814
00:48:56,400 --> 00:48:57,800
This has to stop.

815
00:48:58,480 --> 00:48:59,960
One of us has to go.

816
00:49:14,560 --> 00:49:16,240
You really don't know which?

817
00:49:16,320 --> 00:49:17,600
Let's find out.

818
00:49:19,080 --> 00:49:20,720
Let's do it

819
00:49:20,800 --> 00:49:22,440
like we've done everything else...

820
00:49:24,240 --> 00:49:25,480
Together.

821
00:49:29,200 --> 00:49:31,120
How about we just don't?

822
00:49:31,200 --> 00:49:33,920
Why don't we just fly away somewhere?

823
00:49:34,040 --> 00:49:36,960
-Oh, that'd be great, wouldn't it?
-(BOTH CHUCKLE)

824
00:49:40,200 --> 00:49:41,600
God, yeah.

825
00:49:41,680 --> 00:49:42,720
(LAUGHS)

826
00:49:45,480 --> 00:49:46,920
Good luck, Clara.

827
00:49:48,160 --> 00:49:49,680
Good luck, Doctor.

828
00:49:51,200 --> 00:49:52,840
(BEEPING)

829
00:49:55,880 --> 00:49:57,320
So, what happens now?

830
00:50:01,560 --> 00:50:04,080
I suppose we just, um...
We just wait a minute, I suppose.

831
00:50:04,160 --> 00:50:05,400
One of us...

832
00:50:11,560 --> 00:50:12,920
One of us...

833
00:50:15,080 --> 00:50:17,120
I don't think I could ever forget you.

834
00:50:21,280 --> 00:50:23,360
Clara, I don't think
you're ever gonna have to.

835
00:50:29,560 --> 00:50:30,760
(GASPS)

836
00:50:32,000 --> 00:50:33,000
No.

837
00:50:34,080 --> 00:50:35,960
-Run like hell.
-What?

838
00:50:37,360 --> 00:50:39,000
Run like hell
because you always need to.

839
00:50:39,080 --> 00:50:41,520
Laugh at everything
because it's always funny.

840
00:50:41,600 --> 00:50:43,160
No. Stop it. You're saying goodbye.

841
00:50:43,240 --> 00:50:44,480
Don't say goodbye.

842
00:50:44,560 --> 00:50:47,320
Never be cruel and never be cowardly.

843
00:50:47,400 --> 00:50:51,160
And if you ever are, always make amends.

844
00:50:51,240 --> 00:50:52,560
-(GASPS)
-Stop it!

845
00:50:53,040 --> 00:50:54,600
Stop this... Stop it!

846
00:50:55,200 --> 00:50:57,680
Never eat pears. They're too squishy.

847
00:50:57,760 --> 00:50:58,800
And they always make your chin wet.

848
00:50:58,880 --> 00:51:00,760
That one is quite important,
write it down.

849
00:51:00,840 --> 00:51:02,480
I didn't mean to do this. I'm sorry.

850
00:51:02,560 --> 00:51:04,640
It's okay. (GROANS)

851
00:51:05,440 --> 00:51:06,680
It's okay.

852
00:51:08,000 --> 00:51:09,360
I went too far.

853
00:51:10,040 --> 00:51:11,760
I broke all my own rules.

854
00:51:11,840 --> 00:51:14,080
I became the Hybrid.

855
00:51:14,160 --> 00:51:16,120
This is right!

856
00:51:16,200 --> 00:51:17,760
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

857
00:51:17,840 --> 00:51:19,280
I accept it.

858
00:51:20,560 --> 00:51:21,840
I can't.

859
00:51:24,880 --> 00:51:26,880
There has to be something I can do.

860
00:51:28,640 --> 00:51:29,840
Smile for me.

861
00:51:30,800 --> 00:51:33,400
Go on, Clara Oswald.

862
00:51:34,360 --> 00:51:35,880
One last time.

863
00:51:38,800 --> 00:51:40,200
How could I smile?

864
00:51:44,320 --> 00:51:45,560
It's okay.

865
00:51:46,360 --> 00:51:47,800
Don't you worry.

866
00:51:48,920 --> 00:51:50,200
(SOFTLY) I'll remember you.

867
00:52:09,080 --> 00:52:10,120
Sir.

868
00:52:11,400 --> 00:52:13,200
Are you all right?

869
00:52:15,120 --> 00:52:16,480
Where am I?

870
00:52:20,960 --> 00:52:22,760
How did I get here?

871
00:52:22,840 --> 00:52:24,560
Clara asked me to look after you.

872
00:52:24,640 --> 00:52:26,880
She said you might be a bit upset.

873
00:52:28,040 --> 00:52:29,760
-Clara?
-Yeah.

874
00:52:29,840 --> 00:52:31,360
She was just here.

875
00:52:32,600 --> 00:52:34,240
I don't know where she went.

876
00:52:35,680 --> 00:52:36,960
Clara?

877
00:52:38,120 --> 00:52:39,400
Clara, who?

878
00:52:41,520 --> 00:52:45,560
When something goes missing, you can
always recreate it by the hole it left.

879
00:52:46,760 --> 00:52:49,080
I know her name was Clara.

880
00:52:49,160 --> 00:52:50,960
I know we travelled together.

881
00:52:51,880 --> 00:52:53,880
I know that there was an Ice Warrior
on a submarine

882
00:52:53,960 --> 00:52:55,680
and a Mummy on the Orient Express.

883
00:52:55,760 --> 00:52:58,520
I know we sat together in the Cloisters

884
00:52:58,600 --> 00:53:00,760
and she told me something
very important,

885
00:53:00,840 --> 00:53:02,320
but I've no idea what she said.

886
00:53:04,720 --> 00:53:06,200
Or what she looked like.

887
00:53:07,360 --> 00:53:08,800
Or how she talked.

888
00:53:09,680 --> 00:53:11,040
Or laughed.

889
00:53:14,560 --> 00:53:15,760
There's nothing there.

890
00:53:16,200 --> 00:53:17,480
Just nothing.

891
00:53:21,440 --> 00:53:22,760
Are you looking for her?

892
00:53:25,120 --> 00:53:26,400
I'm trying. (SIGHS)

893
00:53:27,320 --> 00:53:29,040
She could be anyone, right?

894
00:53:29,480 --> 00:53:32,080
You don't know
who you're looking for, I mean...

895
00:53:32,160 --> 00:53:33,960
She could be me, for all you know.

896
00:53:34,640 --> 00:53:36,320
There's one thing I know about her,

897
00:53:36,400 --> 00:53:37,920
just one thing.

898
00:53:38,000 --> 00:53:40,560
If I met her again,
I'd absolutely know her.

899
00:53:43,520 --> 00:53:46,120
I think that we were here, you know.

900
00:53:47,720 --> 00:53:49,720
I think that we were here together once.

901
00:53:50,640 --> 00:53:52,160
I'm sure I remember.

902
00:53:53,760 --> 00:53:55,120
Over here.

903
00:53:57,440 --> 00:53:59,000
Stupid...

904
00:53:59,080 --> 00:54:01,520
Amy and Rory. It was Amy and Rory.

905
00:54:03,600 --> 00:54:05,760
What about your Tardis, eh?

906
00:54:05,840 --> 00:54:07,440
-You found that yet?
-No.

907
00:54:08,440 --> 00:54:10,920
Somebody's moved it from London.
I'm still looking.

908
00:54:12,680 --> 00:54:14,080
But this diner...

909
00:54:15,840 --> 00:54:17,240
It wasn't always here, was it?

910
00:54:18,120 --> 00:54:19,880
It used to be
on the other side of the hill.

911
00:54:19,960 --> 00:54:22,200
Maybe someone will
find your Tardis for you.

912
00:54:28,040 --> 00:54:29,600
(GUITAR STRUMMING)

913
00:54:39,760 --> 00:54:41,720
What Clara told you in the Cloisters...

914
00:54:44,440 --> 00:54:45,960
I don't remember
a single thing about it.

915
00:54:46,040 --> 00:54:47,520
You said, "Memories...

916
00:54:48,280 --> 00:54:51,280
"...become stories when we forget them.”

917
00:54:53,880 --> 00:54:55,720
Maybe some of them become songs.

918
00:54:57,000 --> 00:54:58,720
(GUITAR STRUMMING)

919
00:54:58,800 --> 00:55:00,240
That'd be nice.

920
00:55:05,360 --> 00:55:07,040
Yeah, it would be, wouldn't it?

921
00:55:24,520 --> 00:55:26,520
(TARDIS WHOOSHING)

922
00:55:33,280 --> 00:55:35,080
(WIND WHISTLING)

923
00:55:52,200 --> 00:55:55,000
ASHILDR: I don't think
I've got the chameleon circuit working.

924
00:55:55,080 --> 00:55:57,560
The outer shell might be stuck
as an American diner.

925
00:55:57,640 --> 00:55:58,640
Awesome.

926
00:55:59,640 --> 00:56:00,720
Still no pulse?

927
00:56:02,120 --> 00:56:03,800
(SNIFFS)

928
00:56:03,880 --> 00:56:07,000
Time isn't healing. I'm still frozen.

929
00:56:07,080 --> 00:56:08,080
You know what that means?

930
00:56:08,160 --> 00:56:10,400
It means my death is a fixed event.

931
00:56:10,480 --> 00:56:12,800
The universe depends on it happening.

932
00:56:12,880 --> 00:56:14,040
I'm sorry.

933
00:56:14,120 --> 00:56:15,440
Why?

934
00:56:15,520 --> 00:56:18,000
Why does everybody think I am so scared?

935
00:56:18,080 --> 00:56:20,720
We all face the Raven in the end.
That is the deal.

936
00:56:21,680 --> 00:56:23,960
If I go back to Gallifrey,
they can put me back, right?

937
00:56:24,040 --> 00:56:25,920
On Trap Street,
the moment they took me out?

938
00:56:26,000 --> 00:56:27,080
Of course.

939
00:56:28,800 --> 00:56:30,160
Mind you,

940
00:56:31,400 --> 00:56:32,560
seeing as I'm not actually ageing,

941
00:56:32,640 --> 00:56:35,400
there's still a tiny
little bit of wiggle room, isn't there?

942
00:56:35,480 --> 00:56:37,800
-Wiggle room?
-Wiggle room, yeah.

943
00:56:37,880 --> 00:56:40,240
You know, wiggle room.

944
00:56:40,320 --> 00:56:43,360
We could, um, you know,
stop off on the way.

945
00:56:45,040 --> 00:56:46,760
-Where are we going?
-Gallifrey.

946
00:56:46,840 --> 00:56:48,520
Like I said...

947
00:56:50,200 --> 00:56:51,200
Gallifrey.

948
00:56:51,840 --> 00:56:53,520
(TARDIS WHOOSHING)

949
00:56:54,680 --> 00:56:55,920
The long way round.

950
00:57:44,440 --> 00:57:45,840
(TARDIS POWERING UP)

951
00:58:40,200 --> 00:58:41,440
(WHIRRING)

952
00:59:01,040 --> 00:59:02,600
(TARDIS WHOOSHING)

953
00:59:22,800 --> 00:59:24,800
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

954
00:59:52,480 --> 00:59:53,480
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

955
00:59:54,280 --> 00:59:55,440
Is there anything on my head?

956
00:59:55,600 --> 00:59:57,000
Erm... Well, yes.

957
00:59:58,120 --> 01:00:00,560
-River!
-Death initiating.

958
01:00:01,720 --> 01:00:04,040
Stop holding my hand.
People don't do that to me.

959
01:00:04,120 --> 01:00:05,840
Destroy them!

960
01:00:06,040 --> 01:00:08,080
RIVER: Nobody move! Or the head gets it.

961
01:00:08,440 --> 01:00:10,480
Sonic Trowel? Do you realise
how ridiculous that sounds?

962
01:00:12,640 --> 01:00:15,640
-You planned to take my head?
-Never crossed my mind.

963
01:00:16,200 --> 01:00:17,720
Long live the King.

964
01:00:18,440 --> 01:00:21,160
RIVER: This is a serious mission.
There is nothing to laugh about here.

965
01:00:21,320 --> 01:00:22,800
We're being threatened by a bag!

966
01:00:23,160 --> 01:00:24,440
Give us the treasure!

